document_data.name: Arrabarran Stuffed Fish
document_data.mainbody: '''Arrabarran stuffed fish''' was a morningfeast dish served in [[Arrabar]] of the [[Vilhon Reach]].
document_data.Description: Each fish was stuffed with [[sausage]]s, [[potato]]es, and baked. When cooked until flaky, fish was served, accompanied by [[scrambled eggs]] with [[cheese]] and [[lemon]]-[[wine]] sauce, and hand-ripped fresh [[bread]].
document_data.History: This morningfeast was served to young [[Emriana Matrell|Emriana]] and her grandmother [[Hetta Matrell]] on [[Tarsakh 10]], the {{YearlinkName|1373}}, after the young lady witnessed a murder of two commoners the night before.
